description: Texts contain various forms and uses of the root words "fract", "fra", and "fram", which relate to words such as "fracture", "frame", "frank", and "frat" often in contexts of language, medicine, and technology, and also contain some forms of "frau" or "fran" possibly referring to personal names or cultural references.
Honorifics, titles, and familial terms often used in formal or polite address, such as Madame, Monsieur, Dame, Frau, Sister, Mama, Mamma, and others, often preceding a proper noun or surname.
